Legally Blonde 2: Red, White &amp; Blonde;;2003;;PG-13;;Comedy;;4.8;;Charles Herman-Wurmfeld;;Reese Witherspoon,Sally Field,Bob Newhart,Regina King,Jennifer Coolidge,Bruce McGill,Dana Ivey,Mary Lynn Rajskub,Jessica Cauffiel,Alanna Ubach,J Barton,Stanley Anderson,Bruce Thomas,Luke Wilson,Ruth Williamson,Jack McGee,Amir Talai,Gregorio;;Elle Woods played by Reese Witherspoon is a Harvard lawyer who goes to Washington D.C. to change the law on animal testing. She runs into the political system, the U.S. Congress. Lucky for her, she meets a doorman, Sidney played by Bob Newhart, who shows her how the system works to get a bill passed. She writes `The Bruiser Bill' and puts it in the hopper of Congress. Elle needs 218 signatures to get her bill to be voted on. She gets some unlikely support from several members of Congress she befriends. To get more support, Elle has a Million Dog March on Washington. Douglas Young (the-movie-guy);;https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0333780/